description: Dive into "Love in the Air: Oludeniz Escapes" ‚Äî a handpicked list of places with quick notes, links, and essentials for fast trip planning and discovery.
title: Love in the Air: Oludeniz Escapes

places.generalDescription: Yengec Restaurant is a seafood-focused dining spot, renowned for its crab-based dishes. Situated in a coastal area known for its seafood, the restaurant takes advantage of fresh catches to create flavorful delicacies. Whether it's on Calis Beach or in the secluded location of Gocek, Yengec offers stunning sea views and mouth-watering Turkish dishes.

sources.snippet: For those seeking a more intimate setting, Yengec Restaurant in nearby Gocek offers a secluded location with stunning sea views and mouth-watering Turkish dishes.
sources.shortName: Fethiye, Turkey: A Romantic Destination for Couples

places.name: Yengec Restaurant

reviews.text: Yengec is a wonderful waterfront seafood restaurant in the area. Pretty good wine selection and fresh seafood. You get to choose your own fish. We did the salt crusted bake and it was absolutely delicious!
Absolutely amazing! The seafood was super fresh, everything tasted great, and the view made it even better. Truly enjoyed everything here!

Yenge√ß Restaurant offers an amazing dining experience! I tried various hot and cold mezes, and each one was delicious. The service was superb, and the atmosphere is simply perfect, especially with its location right next to the sea. Highly recommend for anyone looking for a memorable meal in a beautiful setting.

I ended up coming here 3 evenings in a row for dinner and the waiter Oktay really good take care of us every time we visited here. They are very service oriented and one can feel it.

places.generalDescription: √ñl√ºdeniz Beach is a stunning nature reserve known for its tranquil lagoon and picturesque curved beach. It has gained worldwide recognition for its natural beauty, with turquoise waters and a variety of exciting activities such as paragliding, swimming, scuba diving, camping in Butterfly Valley, and off-road safaris.

sources.snippet: The main beach at √ñl√ºdeniz is a long stretch of sand and pebbles, with the lagoon at its northern end. The beach is backed by cafes and restaurants who are ready to provide holiday-makers with food and drink during their sun-filled days.
sources.shortName: 10 Awesome Things To Do In Oludeniz, Turkey

places.name: √ñl√ºdeniz Beach

reviews.text: Great beach, super large with plenty going on in the area. Water was turquoise and crystal clear! Super beautiful, we went in the beginning of may and it was extremely empty and pretty peaceful.

its a really cool place. but be prepared: it is very crowded, they will charge you multiple times for different things. The sun shades are a bit small, you need to adjust your sun-bed constantly (if you have space of course). it has a locker tho' which is really handy, but didn't worked for us, but the staff did a workaround to fix it for us. :)
All together we had a blast at the bay, the water is very clear once you pass the shallow water. and if you up for exploring , you can climb the surrounding ‚Äúmini island‚Äù rocks. i wouldn't miss it!

Beautiful Beach. Love the scenery. It's pebbly, but the pebbles are smooth. Water is crystal clear. Beach has washrooms. Entrance was 100TL per person. No stamp or receipt to leave and come back. Parking is extra. We had a scooter and just parked it outside the gate for free.

places.generalDescription: Oludeniz Blu Luxury Boutique Hotel is an upscale adults-only retreat near the Blue Lagoon, offering chic accommodations with private pools. The hotel stands out with unique amenities such as an on-site gallery, art classes, and a library. Its intimate size provides a more relaxing atmosphere compared to larger resorts. Guests can enjoy special touches like pillow menus and turndown service. The hotel also offers a honeymoon suite as part of a proposal package and some rooms feature swim-up access.

sources.snippet: √ñl√ºdeniz Blu Luxury Unique Hotel - Adults-Only has free bikes, seasonal outdoor swimming pool, a fitness centre and garden in Oludeniz. Ideally set in the Oludeniz City Center district, this hotel provides a bar. All rooms will provide guests with a wardrobe and a kettle.

√ñl√ºdeniz Blu Luxury Unique Hotel is a fantastic four-star establishment that offers adults-only accommodation. You will enjoy easy access to the beach and a beautiful garden. There‚Äôs a restaurant with an exciting menu and a bar serving a wide variety of refreshments.
sources.shortName: 9 Best Adults-Only Hotels In √ñl√ºdeniz, Turkey - Updated 2024

sources.snippet: The hotel is secluded and quiet, offering amazing swim-up pool rooms, a trendy restaurant and an intimate, boutique appeal. It‚Äôs perfect for couples. View this post on Instagram
sources.shortName: The Ultimate Oludeniz Turkey Travel Guide

places.name: Oludeniz Blu Luxury Boutique Hotel

reviews.text: Good hotel and you can walk to the beach, breakfast is so nice, you can watch Paragelaider when you eat breakfast or when you swim‚Ä¶ you can take free bicycles and use lovely and cute library‚Ä¶ the rooms of ground floor have private swimming pool and higher floors have jacuzzi ‚Ä¶ totally is good place and you will have a good accommodations and the staffs are so nice ‚Ä¶. 100 % recommend

HThis is absolutely ridiculous. We stayed for two nights and had the ‚ÄòDo Not Disturb' sign on. When we returned on the second night, we wanted to call the front desk for a bottle of water and some towels. However, we were told that housekeeping had already finished for the day and no services could be provided. They even suggested we go to the bar and pay for water if we were thirsty. Finding this unacceptable, I called the front desk again, only to have my calls hung up on twice. The attitude of the front desk staff was incredibly arrogant.

We ended up going to the front desk in person to speak with the staff and their manager. Although the towels and water were eventually delivered, there was no apology whatsoever. This is basic hotel service, but the front desk's deceitful behavior and the manager's dismissive attitude are completely intolerable! While we still have one night before checkout, I am already furious. The only reason I'm giving one star is because there's no option for zero.

√ñl√ºdeniz blu luxury was comfortable and clean. We were sick majority of our stay so tried out most of the room service menu, most food was good but the calamari and the kebab was terrible and dry. The Turkish ravioli, chicken schnitzel, sweet and sour chicken and fruit platter were our favourites.
The rooms stayed sound proof but we could hear all the people nearby in other rooms, which we didn't mind but could be a deal breaker for some.
The daily buffet was one of the best I've had, with slight variances each day and omelettes made to order we loved getting up each morning to visit the buffet breakfast.
The pool was so nice, but a bit cold and they had good music playing to set the tone.
The staff were very accomodating and helped with everything whether it be organising a taxi, getting a doctor or booking tours etc, which we later had to cancel. The hotel was also within walking distance to the beach, but they offer free push bikes which is good. Just beware the hill back up is slightly difficult without gears on the bike.
Overall we recommend Blu Luxury √ñl√ºdeniz!!

places.generalDescription: Fethiye Bay is a paradise for boating enthusiasts, with its stunning aquamarine waters and uncrowded bays offering a serene sailing experience. The Fethiye Central Fish Market, also known as Balƒ±k Pazarƒ± - Mengi, is a bustling hub where local fishers sell their catch of the day. Visitors can purchase seafood from the round fish counter and have it cooked at nearby restaurants.

sources.snippet: Another must-visit is the iconic Fish Market, where couples can select their own fresh catch and have it cooked to perfection at one of the surrounding restaurants. For those seeking a more intimate setting, Yengec Restaurant in nearby Gocek offers a secluded location with stunning sea views and mouth-watering Turkish dishes.
sources.shortName: Fethiye, Turkey: A Romantic Destination for Couples

places.name: Fethiye Fish Market - Balƒ±k Pazarƒ±

reviews.text: Fethiye fish market is close to the 'old town' arcades of Paspatur, a few minutes' walk from the harbour, and about 30 minutes' walk from the bus station. In the centre are many fishmongers selling their wares for you to take home, or to buy and then have one of the surrounding restaurants cook it for you. The restaurants are all in the same market area. It gets very busy in the evenings, when you may find Turkish musicians playing at tables. The fish is very good value and very fresh every day. It's an enjoyable and interesting experience.

It's a small area where you are approached by various people trying to pull you to their restaurant. The idea is to buy the type of sea food you like and then have a restaurant cook it for you they way you prefer.
The restaurant charges you for cooking your sea food plus upsells you their side dishes.

A bit of a tourist trap. Very hectic and pushy restaurant owners trying very hard to get you to sit at their restaurant. The food is ok, but the fish prices have to be negotiated which is a bit of a pain. There is a strong fishy smell everywhere (it is a fish market, so it's not surprising) which isn't the greatest while eating. It's also quite pricey especially considering the quality was ok at best. Interesting experience, but not a must in my opinion. There are much better places to eat fresh fish in Fethiye. Also the octopus was not good.

places.generalDescription: Barracuda Restaurant Wine & Grill Bar is a must-visit for seafood enthusiasts and those seeking an upscale dining experience. The friendly staff provide a warm welcome, while the culinary offerings exceed expectations. The surf and turf dishes feature perfectly cooked, medium-rare steaks that impress diners. Instead of the anticipated baby potatoes or chips, spaghetti hidden beneath a creamy sauce provides a delightful surprise. The jumbo King prawn starter is larger than expected but incredibly flavorful.

sources.snippet: We had an excellent meal in Barracuda restaurant and highly recommend it!. It features a picturesque garden dining area that‚Äôs lit up on an evening, sometimes hosting live entertainment as you eat. The menu is diverse, including the usual Turkish dishes you‚Äôll get to love, but also Thai cuisine, seafood and juicy steaks.
sources.shortName: The Ultimate Oludeniz Turkey Travel Guide

places.name: Barracuda Restaurant Wine & Grill Bar

reviews.text: Lovely meal. Best burger ever.  Great service and central location but not noisy!  Will come back.

This place is amazing!!! If you are around you have to visit.  Place is cozy and has lovely atmosphere.  Stuff is really nice and friendly.  Great food variety...  I believe everyone will find  something what match his taste.  Starter was tasty as well as our main dishes. And as lover of deserts I was so happy to see espresso creme brule and panacota on the list..  This place is 10/10 for me and my boyfriend.  For sure we will be back some days ‚ù§Ô∏è Thank you so much

That was one of the best dining experiences in my life. I tried grilled sea bass with amazing grilled side vegetables and baby potatoes. My friend also tried a soup of the day and mussels. It was also very tasty.

places.generalDescription: Kidrak Beach, also known as Paradise Beach, is a pristine and picturesque destination with its powdery white sands. Accessible via a nature trail or a charming sailing boat from the nearby Serenity Beach resort, it offers crystal-clear waters and convenient amenities such as wooden paths for easy access. Visitors can enjoy the tranquil atmosphere and rent sunbeds while taking in the beautiful surroundings. The beach provides paid parking facilities and various rental options for added comfort during your visit.
places.name: Kidrak Beach

reviews.text:
We love this beach. There are fine pebbles/coarse sand on the beach, and it is really quiet here. The parking lot is under the trees, the water is fantastic, transparent. It is very nice before and during sunset.
The entrance fee (per car) is only 120 try.

Went here in late April and the beach was very calm with perfect blue water. Just be careful, the water is very deep after 3-4 meters. Parking was 180 Lira and 2 sunbeds with umbrella was 650 lira. Normal priced

Absolutely stunning beach, with fabulous light blue sea water and a sandy beach. It's truly beautiful. We visited at the beginning of July, 2025. There were a lot of people there, but the beach is very big and spacious so it doesn't feel crowded. Sun-beds are comfortable and umbrellas are big. It costs 750 TL for two sun-beds and an umbrella. Thats a reasonable price.
There is a bar and a restaurant there. Prices are also completely fine. The beach has a huge parking area, and a lot of it has shade, which is great. Parking costs 180 TL for the entire day for a car.

places.generalDescription: Ece Marina in Fethiye offers a tranquil and relaxing atmosphere with rows of yachts on the blue waters. Visitors can take a leisurely stroll around the marina to admire the docked boats and enjoy the picturesque views. The marina provides various amenities such as a food shop, restaurant, gas station, clean showers, marine shops, and services. It is praised for its accessibility with supportive staff and beautiful surroundings including mountain views.

sources.snippet: Another must-visit is the iconic Fish Market, where couples can select their own fresh catch and have it cooked to perfection at one of the surrounding restaurants. For those seeking a more intimate setting, Yengec Restaurant in nearby Gocek offers a secluded location with stunning sea views and mouth-watering Turkish dishes.
sources.shortName: Fethiye, Turkey: A Romantic Destination for Couples

places.name: Ece Marina

reviews.text: Expensive? Definitely. But the service is much better than for the most of the other marinas around. Assistance is just great. I felt really comfortable when I stayed there.
There are stores, laundry clean and repairment services around. Is in the center of Fethiye. Very safe. Expensive

the worst gas station I have ever been to. I was asked to stand on a place which was not prepared for mooring - no fenders. Not only did the service pull my mooring line causing my boat lightly hit the pier, but they subsequently called the charter company informing that I have caused damage to the boat (300euros)

places.generalDescription: Oyster Residences is a cozy adults-only hotel located near Oludeniz Beach. The 4-star property offers modern air-conditioned rooms and is situated in a traditional Fethiye stone house surrounded by olive trees. Guests can enjoy the outdoor pool, garden with lounge beds, and free Wi-Fi. The hotel also features multiple dining options including Mimoza Restaurant, Barracuda Restaurant Wine & Grill Bar, and many others.

sources.snippet: Staying at Oyster Residence guarantees you unfettered access to a white, sandy beach. The compound is dotted with olive trees that create an air of tranquility. There is a seasonal outdoor swimming pool where you can sip a refreshing cocktail while relaxing.
sources.shortName: 9 Best Adults-Only Hotels In √ñl√ºdeniz, Turkey - Updated 2024

sources.snippet: A romantic beach side property set in pretty gardens overlooking the beach. Light airy rooms with mosquito net draped beds and large modern bathrooms. A terraced restaurant specialises in Mediterranean seafood.
sources.shortName: Best places to stay in Oludeniz, Turkey (2025)

places.name: Oyster Residences

reviews.text: We had a great experience staying here from 19-22 May 2025. The staff was very kind and the check-in and check-out were smooth. I was a little worried because I had read some reviews about loud music and me and my family of 5 were prepared with our noise cancelling airpods but we didn't use them. We had two rooms on opposite ends and my siblings also slept well. The breakfast was great and the restaurant had delicious options I had their Chicken curry which was amazing! My mother has difficulty walking this was a prime location with everything close by.

Oyster Residences is a Brilliant Hotel‚Ä¶ but not for those who like to sleep at night‚Ä¶

4 star hotel right on the beachside of the tourist town, √ñl√ºdeniz. If you're looking for a paradise setting that'll give your Instagram a serious glow-up, this is the spot for you. The atmosphere in the hotel is very reminiscent of the atmosphere of Hayao Miyazaki's worlds. In this hotel, you can practically roll out of bed and go straight into the sea. But‚Ä¶ that's if you actually get any sleep.

That's the main issue here, the noise. √ñl√ºdeniz, being a tourist hotspot, means there are a lot of nightclubs nearby, and they seem to compete on who can blast their music the loudest at night. The booming bass doesn't stop until around roughly 2:30 AM, so if you're hoping for a peaceful night, think again.  If you enjoy late-night raves or have a deep appreciation for high-decibel beats, you'll fit right in. For the rest of us? Not so much.

My stay included breakfast, breakfast as many of you know opens very early and closes pretty early as well in many hotels. So after a night of listening to nightclub music, you wake up and basically drag yourself half-dead half-alive to this breakfast, since you paid for it. Speaking of breakfast, it's a mix of self-service and waiter-ordered options. You can get fresh fruit, pancakes, and juice yourself. As well as, order your desired breakfast. They don't have a menu, so you will have to figure it out yourself what exactly you want for breakfast.

The rooms are cozy, with a charming wooden design that fits the "dream holiday" vibe perfectly. However, if you get an attic room like I did, be prepared to whack your head on the oddly angled ceiling good few times. Room do have an air conditioning which you can turn on and off, but air conditioning is aimed directly at the bed, which can lead to a stiff neck or even catching a cold if you're not careful.

Another thing to mention, all guest rooms are located in different buildings and require stairs to reach your desired room. So if you are traveling with person who uses wheelchair, or elderly person or any person who has injuries, this hotel will not be a good option for you. Even first floor rooms will require you to climb a few steps.

On the bright side, this hotel features a stunning outdoor pool surrounded by olive trees. It's easily my personal highlight of the stay in this hotel.

Another thing I want to note, is the parking... The hotel does offer parking on its promises, but it's sooooo tiny, and cars are crammed in like sardines in the can. So you are required to give the keys to the receptionist when staying in the hotel, so they can shuffle cars around. So If you're a little paranoid about your car or your stuff inside, you might want to think twice. I'm just saying, the cars parked a few cm to each other.

Overall, Oyster Residences is a beautiful hotel for a dream summer holiday, perfect for beach lovers and Instagrammers. Just be ready for a few sleepless nights and minor annoyances along the way.

We stayed here for six nights in the third week of August and had a lovely experience overall. The hotel has a perfect location, right in front of the beach. Our room was very clean and sufficient, just with a slight damp smell, but nothing major. Upon arrival, we were kindly upgraded from a standard room to one with a terrace facing the pool, which was a very nice gesture.

Breakfast was tasty and sufficient, and the staff were always friendly and helpful, making us feel very comfortable. The atmosphere of the hotel is cozy and charming, and the beach is clean and beautiful. In the evenings, of course, you can hear music from outside, but it didn't bother us at all. After spending the day exploring and swimming, we slept very well at night.

The only downside is the overall busyness of the area. Parking the car or waiting for it to be taken out sometimes took time, but this is not the hotel's fault-it's just how crowded √ñl√ºdeniz is in general.

If you're planning to spend most of your time outside and on the beach rather than in the room, this is a very sweet, convenient boutique hotel. We really enjoyed our stay and are grateful for the kind service. üåø

places.generalDescription: Oludeniz Sun City Beach Club is a top resort in the Oludeniz and Fethiye Bay area, offering a private beach, pools, and activities suitable for all ages. The hotel provides options for both solo travelers and families, with the choice of booking a private zone for adults only or an ordinary one. It's conveniently located just 25 minutes away from Oludeniz beach, with shuttle buses available to take guests to the beach or taxis at reasonable prices.
places.name: Suncity Beach Club

reviews.text:
Keep driving right to the end of thw road and you reach this magical place.
Safe for your kids as its part of the blue lagoon and pefect for a swim in the out of season months as warmer than the swimming pools.
Absolutely awesomw staff and atmosphere ,i love it here, its my go to place whenever i'm in fethiye Costs roughly about ¬£10 each and theres a restaurant whoch is excellent and reasonably priced, not as cheap as less touristy places downtown but the food is well worth the monry. The music is very chilled (think 90's ibiza chill out music) which is perfect background acoustics. you may need a car, or at least to get the bus and then walk. Plenty of parking and well the views. Its just so good. Closes at 5pm and the beach is so much cleaner than other places. I hope it keeps the standards up, been going about ten years so far and its still good to be fair which is impressive in itself, keep up the excellent standards 'suncity' top marks

location (created by nature) is good - shade from trees, beautiful lagoon. but territory is not clean, and not taken care enough. Good  selection of activities - sup boards, catamarans etc on extra charge. Some days can be too crowdy and noisy with too many kids, there is +16 space on the beach for extra cost.

Very nice beach club with lots of sun beds, access to a shallow water sand beach and many trees for natural shade.
The Adult section is an excellent idea to hope having a quiet and relax time, but they should apply it in the water as well as nothing prevents noisy infants to play in the sand and water literally 5 meters from your expensive ‚Äúadult only zone‚Äù sun bed. And even if not the case, kids constantly screaming in the water will disturb the relax time you were hoping to get in the adult only zone‚Ä¶too bad as the site is fantastic and the lounge music well chosen.
